"Cloud is inefficient look at this data and see how inefficient it is versus my own servers"

"Cloud is not secure"

"Cloud is just someone else's computer"

This is why we're extra pumped to be working on @bigwhalelabs together.

We're building a future where any contributor wherever they come from can ~all~ make it, not just the platform itself.

That's why web 3 and blockchain are crucial. 

We need *transparency* by design and more alignment between value creators and platforms.

And as @cdixon puts it:

https://t.co/rNDOl0uQ2D

This is after Pavel the founder of Telegram promised in 2016, $1M towards bot developers.

Only a handful of devs ever got paid, and there hasn't been a transparent update or ledger of funding.

 https://t.co/iqxvihEeRP

Over 3 Million groups use his products: improving UX, fighting spammers, and more. 

His voice-to-text bot has translated *25 years* of speech to text. 

Yet not a single cent has been paid to him for this work by the platform he builds value for.
